## Proposed Changes

### 1. Auth Store — Disable Auto-Login

#### [MODIFY] [authStore.ts](file:///c:/Users/shash/SafeHerApp/mobile/store/authStore.ts)

- `restoreSession()` currently reads the stored `userId` and calls `getUserById()` → auto-logs in.
- **Change**: Instead of restoring a full session, only read the stored `phone` (for convenience pre-fill) and immediately set `isLoggedIn: false`. The user always sees the login screen.
- Add a `savedPhone` field to the store so the login screen can pre-fill it.
- Keep `logout()` (it already clears storage).

---

### 2. Login Screen — Pre-fill Phone & Remove Auto-Skip

#### [MODIFY] [login.tsx](file:///c:/Users/shash/SafeHerApp/mobile/app/auth/login.tsx)

- Read `savedPhone` from auth store on mount and pre-fill the phone input.
- The user only needs to type their password.
- No other UI changes needed (register link already exists).

---

### 3. Settings — Add "Edit Profile" Section

#### [MODIFY] [settings.tsx](file:///c:/Users/shash/SafeHerApp/mobile/app/settings.tsx)

Add a new **👤 PROFILE** section above the logout button, replacing the static user card with an editable version:

- **Name** — text input with pencil icon
- **Email** — text input
- **Blood Group** — chip selector (same style as register screen)
- **Save button** → calls `authStore.updateProfile({ name, email, blood_group })`
- Show success toast on save

The existing `authStore.updateProfile()` and database `updateUserProfile()` functions already handle saving — we just need the UI.

---

### 4. Background SOS — Enable Voice by Default + Status Card

#### [MODIFY] [settingsStore.ts](file:///c:/Users/shash/SafeHerApp/mobile/store/settingsStore.ts)

- Change default `voiceKeyword: false` → **`voiceKeyword: true`**
- This activates voice spike-detection from first launch without the user needing to find the toggle

#### [MODIFY] [settings.tsx](file:///c:/Users/shash/SafeHerApp/mobile/app/settings.tsx)

Add a **🛡️ BACKGROUND PROTECTION** status card at the top of Settings (just below the user card) showing live status badges:

```
🟢 Shake Detection  ACTIVE
🟢 Voice Detection  ACTIVE   (or 🔴 OFF if disabled)
🟢 Fall Detection   ACTIVE   (or 🔴 OFF if disabled)
🟢 Foreground Guard RUNNING  (always shown)
```

This makes it clear the background detection is working without the user having to dig through settings.

#### [MODIFY] [_layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/shash/SafeHerApp/mobile/app/_layout.tsx)

- No sensor hook changes needed — `useShakeDetection`, `useVoiceDetection`, `useFallDetection`, `useSOSDispatch` are already mounted globally.
- Add mic + accelerometer **permission requests** at startup (before the hooks run) so Android doesn't silently deny them.

